<ns1119:section xmlns:ns1119="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.evaluating.solms.methodology.elicitation">

  <ns1120:title xmlns:ns1120="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Elicitation</ns1120:title>
  <ns1121:para xmlns:ns1121="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
     During this phase the business vision, goals, the desired quality attributes and the
     chosen architecture are communicated.
    The core steps during the elicitation phase are
    <ns1122:orderedlist xmlns:ns1122="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns1123:listitem xmlns:ns1123="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1124:para xmlns:ns1124="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Understand the business drivers.</ns1124:para></ns1123:listitem>
      <ns1125:listitem xmlns:ns1125="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1126:para xmlns:ns1126="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Understand the implemented architecture.</ns1126:para></ns1125:listitem>
      <ns1127:listitem xmlns:ns1127="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1128:para xmlns:ns1128="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Identify architectural approaches.</ns1128:para></ns1127:listitem>
      <ns1129:listitem xmlns:ns1129="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1130:para xmlns:ns1130="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Generate a quality attribute utility tree.</ns1130:para></ns1129:listitem>
      <ns1131:listitem xmlns:ns1131="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1132:para xmlns:ns1132="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Analyze architectural approaches.</ns1132:para></ns1131:listitem>
    </ns1122:orderedlist>
  </ns1121:para>
  
  <ns1133:section xmlns:ns1133="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1134:title xmlns:ns1134="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Understand the business drivers</ns1134:title>
    <ns1135:para xmlns:ns1135="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      If the architecture to be validated is for a system which was developed in the context
      of a project guided by a Vision &amp; Scope document for that project, then 
      we typically start by extracting the following information from that document:
      <ns1136:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1136="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1137:listitem xmlns:ns1137="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1138:para xmlns:ns1138="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the vision the organization is trying to realize with the project,</ns1138:para></ns1137:listitem>
        <ns1139:listitem xmlns:ns1139="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1140:para xmlns:ns1140="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the core stake holders of the project,</ns1140:para></ns1139:listitem>
        <ns1141:listitem xmlns:ns1141="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1142:para xmlns:ns1142="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the business objectives,</ns1142:para></ns1141:listitem>
        <ns1143:listitem xmlns:ns1143="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1144:para xmlns:ns1144="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the financial context including a return on investment estimation,</ns1144:para></ns1143:listitem>
        <ns1145:listitem xmlns:ns1145="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1146:para xmlns:ns1146="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the core use cases (functional requirements) of the system,</ns1146:para></ns1145:listitem>
        <ns1147:listitem xmlns:ns1147="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1148:para xmlns:ns1148="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the core limitations (exclusions),</ns1148:para></ns1147:listitem>
        <ns1149:listitem xmlns:ns1149="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1150:para xmlns:ns1150="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the architectural drivers (i.e. the quality attributes which are important too business),</ns1150:para></ns1149:listitem>
        <ns1151:listitem xmlns:ns1151="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1152:para xmlns:ns1152="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">any constraints placed on the project or the architecture, and</ns1152:para></ns1151:listitem>
        <ns1153:listitem xmlns:ns1153="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1154:para xmlns:ns1154="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">any dependencies the project may have on other projects.</ns1154:para></ns1153:listitem>
      </ns1136:itemizedlist>
    </ns1135:para>
    <ns1155:para xmlns:ns1155="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Should not all the above information be contained in a <ns1156:emphasis xmlns:ns1156="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vision &amp; Scope
      document</ns1156:emphasis>, or should the latter not be available, then the above information
      will be elicited from Management and Business Analysis. 
    </ns1155:para>
  </ns1133:section>
  
  <ns1157:section xmlns:ns1157="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1158:title xmlns:ns1158="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Understanding the architecture</ns1158:title>
    <ns1159:para xmlns:ns1159="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       The lead architect provides the essence of the architecture in a concise, structured way.
       The presentation is expected to have <ns1160:quote xmlns:ns1160="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1161:emphasis xmlns:ns1161="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">a low signal to noise ratio</ns1161:emphasis></ns1160:quote>
       in the sense that it should focus on the architectural core and not stray into auxiliary details.
       The presentation should cover
       <ns1162:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1162="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns1163:listitem xmlns:ns1163="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1164:para xmlns:ns1164="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
           the context of the architecture which covers the environment in which the system
           will live/ is living,
         </ns1164:para></ns1163:listitem>
         <ns1165:listitem xmlns:ns1165="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1166:para xmlns:ns1166="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
           the technical constraints (<ns1167:abbrev xmlns:ns1167="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">e.g.</ns1167:abbrev> the required deployment platforms and
           middleware technologies),
         </ns1166:para></ns1165:listitem>
         <ns1168:listitem xmlns:ns1168="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1169:para xmlns:ns1169="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
           the architectural approaches including
           <ns1170:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1170="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
             <ns1171:listitem xmlns:ns1171="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1172:para xmlns:ns1172="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">any reference architecture employed,</ns1172:para></ns1171:listitem>
             <ns1173:listitem xmlns:ns1173="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1174:para xmlns:ns1174="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the architectural patterns which were enlisted,</ns1174:para></ns1173:listitem>
             <ns1175:listitem xmlns:ns1175="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1176:para xmlns:ns1176="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the tactics which were realized.</ns1176:para></ns1175:listitem>
           </ns1170:itemizedlist>
         </ns1169:para></ns1168:listitem>
       </ns1162:itemizedlist>
       Very commonly a template for documenting architectures is conceptually followed (for example       
       the RUP template).
    </ns1159:para>
  </ns1157:section>
  
  <ns1177:section xmlns:ns1177="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1178:title xmlns:ns1178="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Identify architectural approaches</ns1178:title>
    <ns1179:para xmlns:ns1179="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       This step a discussion with the lead architect and the architecture team in order to
       <ns1180:emphasis xmlns:ns1180="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">verify and deepen and broaden the architectural understanding</ns1180:emphasis>.
       Usually the use further architectural patterns is identified.
    </ns1179:para>
  </ns1177:section>
  
  <ns1181:section xmlns:ns1181="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1182:title xmlns:ns1182="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Generate a quality attribute utility tree</ns1182:title>
    <ns1183:para xmlns:ns1183="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      This is perhaps the core step within ATAM. In this step one generates
      <ns1184:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1184="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1185:listitem xmlns:ns1185="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1186:para xmlns:ns1186="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          a utility tree containing the quality attributes and the scenarios they affect, and
        </ns1186:para></ns1185:listitem>
        <ns1187:listitem xmlns:ns1187="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1188:para xmlns:ns1188="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          a prioritized list of scenarios extracted from the utility tree.  
        </ns1188:para></ns1187:listitem>
      </ns1184:itemizedlist>
    </ns1183:para>
    
    <ns1189:section xmlns:ns1189="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns1190:title xmlns:ns1190="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Utility trees</ns1190:title>
      <ns1191:para xmlns:ns1191="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        Utility trees have 
        <ns1192:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1192="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns1193:listitem xmlns:ns1193="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1194:para xmlns:ns1194="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            a quality attribute at their root,    
          </ns1194:para></ns1193:listitem>
          <ns1195:listitem xmlns:ns1195="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1196:para xmlns:ns1196="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            refined attributes in the next layer of the tree, and  
          </ns1196:para></ns1195:listitem>
          <ns1197:listitem xmlns:ns1197="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1198:para xmlns:ns1198="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            scenarios which have a dependency on that quality attribute in the third layer.  
          </ns1198:para></ns1197:listitem>
        </ns1192:itemizedlist>
        As such they are often shown in tabular form.
      </ns1191:para>
      <ns1199:para xmlns:ns1199="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        In <ns1200:xref xmlns:ns1200="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="resources.information.concepts.architecture.evaluating.atam.methodology.elicitation.utilityTree_tbl"/>
        we show the utility of one quality attribute. Usually a table of multiple utility trees is generated.
        <ns1201:table xmlns:ns1201="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.evaluating.atam.methodology.elicitation.utilityTree_tbl">
          <ns1202:title xmlns:ns1202="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">A fragment of the utility trees for the COFLoader project</ns1202:title>
          <ns1203:tgroup xmlns:ns1203="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" cols="3">
            <ns1204:thead xmlns:ns1204="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              <ns1205:row xmlns:ns1205="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns1206:entry xmlns:ns1206="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Quality attribute</ns1206:entry>
                <ns1207:entry xmlns:ns1207="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Attribute refinement</ns1207:entry>
                <ns1208:entry xmlns:ns1208="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Scenarios</ns1208:entry>
              </ns1205:row>
            </ns1204:thead>
            <ns1209:tbody xmlns:ns1209="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              <ns1210:row xmlns:ns1210="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns1211:entry xmlns:ns1211="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Modifiability</ns1211:entry>
                <ns1212:entry xmlns:ns1212="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                  <ns1213:para xmlns:ns1213="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Flexibility to modify confidence level matching. 
                  </ns1213:para>
                  <ns1214:para xmlns:ns1214="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Flexibility to change data cleansing algorithm.
                  </ns1214:para>
                </ns1212:entry>
                <ns1215:entry xmlns:ns1215="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                  <ns1216:para xmlns:ns1216="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Modify field weightings.
                  </ns1216:para>
                  <ns1217:para xmlns:ns1217="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Replace rules engine for short-list selection.
                  </ns1217:para>
                  <ns1218:para xmlns:ns1218="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Modify required confidence level.
                  </ns1218:para>
                  <ns1219:para xmlns:ns1219="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Modify confidence level matching algorithm.
                  </ns1219:para>
                </ns1215:entry>
              </ns1210:row>
            </ns1209:tbody>
          </ns1203:tgroup>
        </ns1201:table>
      </ns1199:para>
    </ns1189:section>
    
  </ns1181:section>
  
  <ns1220:section xmlns:ns1220="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1221:title xmlns:ns1221="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Analyze architectural approaches</ns1221:title>
    <ns1222:para xmlns:ns1222="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The scenarios are analyzed one by one in priority order:
      <ns1223:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1223="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1224:listitem xmlns:ns1224="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1225:para xmlns:ns1225="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          The architect is asked to explain how the architecture supports each scenario.  
        </ns1225:para></ns1224:listitem>
        <ns1226:listitem xmlns:ns1226="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1227:para xmlns:ns1227="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          The team identifies and documents the architectural decisions with their
          risks, non-risks, sensitivity points and trade offs.  
        </ns1227:para></ns1226:listitem>
      </ns1223:itemizedlist>
    </ns1222:para>
  </ns1220:section>
  
</ns1119:section>